title: Big Desert Wilderness - Plants
description: Incorporating Yanac-Murrayville roadside, road to Red Bluff and down to Broken Bucket.

items.title: Leucopogon cordifolius
items.content_text: Plants mostly completely covered with flowers.

items.title: Boronia coerulescens subsp. coerulescens
items.content_text: Surprised me to see a few plants flowering this time of year (June). Third pic shows blue(-ish) bud that gives rise to the plant's common name.

items.title: Wahlenbergia spp.
items.content_text: Seems to key out to tumidifructa?

items.title: Goodenia spp.
items.content_text: G. robusta (stem too short?) or G. willisiana (leaf too wide?)?

items.title: Dillwynia hispida
items.content_text: Long peduncles is a good ID feature.

items.title: Thelymitra alcockiae
items.content_text: No notch in hood and pink bracts. Not sure of ID. 3rd pic was a plant seen an hour later.

items.title: Thelymitra nuda
items.content_text: Notch in hood suggests nuda. Not sure of ID.

items.title: Allocasuarina spp.
items.content_text: Probably mackliniana subsp xerophila or muelleriana subsp muelleriana?

items.title: Boronia coerulescens subsp. coerulescens, Grevillea lavandula...
Thelymitra alcockiae
items.content_text: Two plants in close proximity, same coloured bracts but different colour on the underside of sepals. Pink bract sems to fit with T. alcockiae.

items.title: Dillwynia sericea, Trichocolletes venustus
items.content_text: Trichocolletes venustus is hundreds of km outside its previously known range.

items.title: Grevillea ilicifolia
items.content_text: Two plants a few kilometres apart.

items.title: Castiarina decemmaculata, Spyridium subochreatum var. subochr...
items.content_text: Beetle is possibly Castiarina sp. (thanks SJ)?
